# Serving llms.txt on Wix

Wix doesn't support placing static files in your web root or setting up proxy routes directly, so you'll need to use **Cloudflare Workers** (or a similar CDN) to proxy the request. [1]

## Steps:

1. **Get your proxy URL from the Setup tab** (where you are now)
   - Look for the proxy URL format: `https://geo.flowblinq.com/api/serve/{your-slug}/llms.txt`

2. **Set up a Cloudflare Worker** to proxy requests
   - If you don't have Cloudflare, point your Wix domain to Cloudflare's nameservers (free tier available)
   - Create a Worker route that intercepts `yourwixsite.com/llms.txt` and forwards it to the proxy URL above

3. **The Worker code is simple:**
   ```javascript
   export default {
     async fetch(request) {
       const url = new URL(request.url);
       if (url.pathname === '/llms.txt') {
         return fetch('https://geo.flowblinq.com/api/serve/{your-slug}/llms.txt');
       }
       return fetch(request);
     }
   };
   ```

4. **Also add routes for:**
   - `/llms-full.txt` → `https://geo.flowblinq.com/api/serve/{your-slug}/llms-full.txt`
   - `/.well-known/ucp.json` → `https://geo.flowblinq.com/api/serve/{your-slug}/business.json`

This keeps all files automatically updated when you re-run audits. [1]

**Need help setting up Cloudflare?** Email hello@flowblinq.ai — they can walk you through it.
